tags.note: Added to underline that this road piece is meant to be used as "three-point turn place" and not as a parking spot.

The access could probably be "yes", however there is a gate that can be closed to block off this entire section (hence "permissive"). It is assumed people will walk/drive here, as there is an information sign at the parking area near the lighthouse.

tags.description: Access path to the fog signal - this section has a guard rail along its entirety and has some steep sections with stairs. Narrow and slightly boggy terrain to be expected.
tags.name: Route to fog signal

tags.description: Path through a pasture - can be quite boggy and harder to see in places. Follow the powerlines until you find a small bridge over a stream.
